############################################################ # Body ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML True or False. a. The discriminant is part of the quadratic formula. [_]{$True}{5}
a. We use the discriminant to calculate the solutions of a quadratic equation. [_]{$TF}{5}
a. If the discriminant is negative, both [`x`]-intercepts of the graph are negative. [_]{$TF}{5}
a. If a quadratic equation won't factor, its graph has no [`x`]-intercepts. [_]{$TF}{5}
