BEGIN_PGML Francine bought a cup of cocoa at the cafeteria. The cocoa cooled off rapidly at first, and then gradually approached room temperature. Which graph more accurately reflects the temperature of the cocoa as a function of time? [_]{$ab}{5}
Explain why. (Select all that apply.)
[@$explain->print_a() @]*
END_PGML ANS(checkbox_cmp($explain->correct_ans()));
BEGIN_PGML
Is the graph you chose concave up or concave down? [_]{$concavity}{5}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION (a): The graph has a steep negative slope at first, corresponding to an initial rapid drop in the temperature of the cocoa. The graph becomes closer to a horizontal line, corresponding to the cocoa approaching room temperature. The graph is concave up.
END_PGML_SOLUTION
