BEGIN_PGML Solve [`2(5x + 3)^2 = 38`] by extracting roots.
a. Give your answers as exact values, separating the solutions with a comma.
[_]{$exact}{25}
Note: Enter "sqrt(2)" to get [`\sqrt{2}\text{,}`] and take care to use parentheses appropriately.
Use the "Preview My Answers" button to see if you have entered valid syntax.
a. Find approximations for the solutions to two decimal places, separating the solutions with a comma.
[_]{$approx}{15}
END_PGML
############################################################ # Solution ############################################################
BEGIN_PGML_SOLUTION a. [`x=\dfrac{-3\pm \sqrt{19}}{5} `]
a. [`x\approx -1.47`] or [`x\approx 0.27`]
END_PGML_SOLUTION
############################################################ # End Problem ############################################################
